Retired footballer Teko Modise is about to be booted from his multimillion-rand Joburg home by SB Guarantee Company for allegedly dribbling it of its bond repayments. Modise, whose credit profile was negatively affected when he lost his houses and cars due to non-payment about five years ago, entered into an agreement with the guarantor in March 2015 to secure a home loan for him. TO READ MORE ON THIS STORY GET A COPY OF TODAY'S SUNDAY WORLD